content.description: One of the easier bolted lines in the canyon. Fun, easy climbing on great rock in an area with amazing views.
content.location: This route is just right of Not Bad For a Little Fuzzball. The first bolt is a bit high, but the climbing up to is really easy. It climbs up a sort of mini buttress.

content.description:
The left line up the south face of Endor. Just like the shuttle "Tydirium", you got to be a bit sneaky on this one. It keeps your attention all the way through.

The crux comes as you try to pass the second bolt but there is a wonderful pocket for you right hand if you look for it.

Very similar to the slab on Milky Way Left Wall.
content.protection: 4 bolts and chains. The moves to the second bolt are harder than you might think. Be careful here.

content.description:
Another good easy one. Good holds lead past the first bolt where it gets a bit interesting. Search around and you find some pretty good holds. And they just get better the higher you go.

**currently joins Ewok Babies to it's chains but is being planned to be the route that goes to the top of the wall.
content.location: The first route past the SW ridge of Endor (just left of Warm Fuzzy Ewok Babies)

climbs.name: Not Bad for a Little Fuzz Ball

content.description: The first completed route on Endor wall. A fun jaunt over small roofs on good juggy holds. A great lead for a new leader or a quick warmup for the many new routes that will be completed very soon.
content.location: Turn the obvious large S. ridge of Endor and walk almost to the first big tree right up against the wall. The route begins right of this tree. There is a new landing built off the trail for this wall.

content.description: A mildly tricky start in which the holds subsequent to the starting edges are slightly hard to find, followed by lower-angled terrain with positive edges (including a sidepull or two, if so inclined) to the top.
content.location:
